β- Caryophyllene, β- myrcene, D-limonene, and linalool standards were purchased from 
TCI
(
Japan
). (E)-β- Farnesene and α- pinene standards were purchased from Wako (
Japan
) and obtained from Dr. Ehrenstorfer GmbH (
Germany
), respectively.

All recombinant proteins were purified using an Ni-NTA Superflow Column (QIAGEN, 
Germany
). After equilibration in 10 mM phosphate buffered saline containing imidazole (PBS-imidazole, pH 7.2), the samples were loaded onto the column. The unbound protein was washed with 20 mM PBS-imidazole (pH 7.2), and the target protein was eluted with 300 mM PBS-imidazole (pH 7.2). Approximately 2.5 mL of eluted protein was mixed and dialyzed on PD-10 desalting columns according to the manufacturer’ s protocol. The protein concentration was determined through the Bradford method, with bovine serum albumin used as the standard.
